<section class="route partner-positions">

  <h2>MANAGE POSITIONS</h2>
  
  <div class="partner-columns">
    <div class="partner-column">  
      <p>
        The BCYF Youth Engagement and Employment Summer Jobs Program has allocated you a 
        total of {{model.positions.length}} positions. You may select 100% of your positions
        ({{model.positions.length}} youth) to work for you this summer. In the list below, 
        browse through applicants who have an interest in the position or area of work you 
        offer. Starting April 5th, you may review candidates and mark "Intend to Hire" or 
        "I do not want to hire." Any remaining youth applicants enter in the jobs lottery.
      </p>

      <p> 
        Please add your choices beginning April 5th and no later than April 28th. Your 
        selections create and official record of who you want to hire. It is mandatory to 
        select applicants by April 28th to complete legal and HR requirements for
      </p>

      <div class="selection-counter">
        Our records show that you intend to hire these applicants. You have {{_}} 
        of {{model.positions.length}} left:
      </div>

      <div class="selected-table">
        <div class="row header-row">
          <div class="column">Name</div>
          <div class="column">Position</div>
          <div class="column">Status</div>
        </div>

        {{#each model.applicants as |applicant|}}
          <div class="row">   
            <div class="colum">{{applicant.fullName}}</div>
            <div class="column">
              <select>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="column">Offer Sent</div>
            <div class="column">
              <button class="small" onclick={{action 'removeApplicant' applicant}}>REMOVE</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        {{/each}}

        <button class="dark" onclick={{action 'submitForm'}}>SUBMIT</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="partner-column">  
      {{outlet}}
    </div>
  </div>


</section>
